The paper deals with the problem of secure communication in the presence of a wiretapper, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of distortion and reliability criteria suggests a focus on signal processing (cs.SI) and communication networks (cs.CC). Finally, the consideration of limiting the number of guesses may involve machine learning (cs.LG) techniques.
